href="gr-000G.xml"
addr="gr-000G"
title="Group">Group</fr:link>. A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Composition Series</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> is a finite sequence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_{i}]]></fr:tex> of subgroups of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> such that
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {1}_{G}=H_{0}\mathrel {\triangleleft } H_{1}\mathrel {\triangleleft }…\mathrel {\triangleleft } H_{n}=G,]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_{i}\mathrel {\triangleleft } H_{i+1}]]></fr:tex> for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i=0,…,n-1]]></fr:tex>, and in particular <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_{i+1}/H_{i}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-003W.xml"
addr="gr-003W"
title="Simple">Simple</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p><fr:strong>Note:</fr:strong> There is no requirement that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_{i}]]></fr:tex> is a normal subgroup of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> except for when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i=n-1]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
